r Vascular Amputations<\/li><li>20% Risk for Traumatic Amputations<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-ebe662d elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"ebe662d\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-01a427b\" data-id=\"01a427b\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a671c94 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"a671c94\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Transtibial \u2013 Below-Knee Amputation (BKA)<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-3fbc5a8 elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"3fbc5a8\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-ca5056f\" data-id=\"ca5056f\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-82afece elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"82afece\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Posterior Flap Technique<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Skin\/Fascia Incision:<ul><li>\u201cTwo-Thirds\/One-Third\u201d Approach<\/li><li>Anterior Incision:<ul><li>Two-Thirds of Leg Circumference<\/li><li>Start Just Past the Planned Tibia Incision<\/li><li>Straight Transverse Incision<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Posterior Incision:<ul><li>One-Third of Leg Circumference<\/li><li>Flap Length: Additional One-Third of Leg Circumference<\/li><li>Slightly Curved Incision<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Bone Transection:<ul><li>Tibia: \u2265 12-15 cm Below Tibial Tuberosity<\/li><li>Fibula: 1-2 cm Proximal to the Tibia<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Neurovascular Management:<ul><li>Major Blood Vessels: Suture Ligate<ul><li>Consider Tourniquet to Decrease Blood Loss<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Nerves: Divide Sharply &amp; Allow Retraction<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Modification &amp; Closure:<ul><li>Bevel Bones to Avoid Sharp Edges \u2013 Particularly the Anterior Tibia<\/li><li>Consider Myodesis of Gastrocnemius to Tibia<\/li><li>Irrigate Prior to Closure<\/li><li>Close Deep Fascia with Interrupted Absorbable Suture<\/li><li>Close Skin with Staples<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>BKA Wound Dressing<\/strong><\/p><ul><li><em>Soft Gauze with Elastic Wrap<\/em><ul><li>Most Commonly Used<\/li><li>Remain Non-Weight Bearing for 4-6 Weeks Until Fit for Prosthesis<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Thigh-Level Rigid Plaster Cast<\/em><ul><li>Shorter Rehabilitation Times<\/li><li>Similar Pain, Healing Rates &amp; Prosthetic Use<\/li><li>Can Include a Temporary Immediate Postoperative Prosthesis (IPOP)<ul><li>May Have Improved Primary Wound Healing &amp; Shorter Rehabilitation Times<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-2f166cc\" data-id=\"2f166cc\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-becf4e2 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"becf4e2\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-12702 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/BKA-Incision.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1692\" height=\"1188\" srcset=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/BKA-Incision.jpg 1692w, https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/BKA-Incision-300x211.jpg 300w, https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/BKA-Incision-1024x719.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/BKA-Incision-768x539.jpg 768w, https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/BKA-Incision-1536x1078.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1692px) 100vw, 1692px\" \/><\/p><p>BKA Incision<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/d